text: Pyrene punctata, common name : the telescoped dove shell, is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Columbellidae, the dove snails. ==Description== The shell size varies between 14 mm and 26 mm ==Distribution== This species is distributed in the Western Pacific and along Australia. ==References== ==External links== * Category:Columbellidae Category:Gastropods described in 1789
title: Pyrene punctata
